#!/usr/bin/env ssc
---
name: effect-imported-handler
---

# effect performed in an imported module, run by an imported handler

Regression for the JS backend (emit-js standalone). An effectful function in an
*imported* module (`query` performing `Box.read`) was not recognised as effectful
by the importer's codegen, so its op lowered to a generic `_dispatch` and the
`_Perform` suspension leaked into the fold (`arr.reduce is not a function`); once
recognised, an effect-performing call inside the handler-body thunk got
`_run`-wrapped and threw "Unhandled effect". The childGen now runs the effect
analysis on the imported module, and an effectful lambda emits a CPS body.

[query, Acc, runBox](./lib/effect-box.ssc)

```scalascript
println(runBox(() => query(0, Acc(0, (a, b) => a + b))))
println(runBox(() => query(0, Acc(100, (a, b) => a + b))))
```
